Website assets repository

| Folder / File  | Description                                                                                    |
| -------------- | ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| **000/**       | EHBEA logo files.                                                                              |
| **00/**        | Official EHBEA documents and forms (e.g., governance, policies, templates).                    |
| **01_YYYY/**   | Conference-related materials, organized by year (e.g., `01_2025` for the 2025 conference).     |
| **photos/**    | Member and participant photos, named by individualsâ€™ last names for easy reference.            |
| **.jpg files** | All image files are stored in `.jpg` format for consistency across the site and documentation. |

Naming Conventions
- Logos: stored in 000/, named descriptively (e.g., ehbea_logo_main.jpg).
- Documents: stored in 00/, use short, descriptive filenames (e.g., membership_form.pdf).
- Conferences: folders are prefixed with 01_ followed by EHBEA- and the year (e.g., 01_EHBEA-2023).
- Photos: named by last name only (e.g., smith.jpg).

These assets are used to:
- Populate and maintain the EHBEA website
- Support annual conference pages and promotional materials
- Provide publicly accessible official documents and forms

Contributing & Upload Instructions
- Clone or download the repository: git clone https://github.com/ehbea/website-assets.git
- Add new assets to the appropriate folder, following the naming conventions above.
-  Commit your changes with a clear message:
git add .
git commit -m "Add 2025 conference banner and updated membership form"
git push
- Submit a pull request (PR) if you are not an administrator.
- Ensure all new images are in .jpg format and under 500 KB for web optimization.

Notes
- All assets are intended for official EHBEA use only.
- Please maintain the existing folder structure and file naming conventions when adding new files.
- Non-logo images should be optimized for web use (preferably under 500 KB).

About EHBEA
- The European Human Behaviour and Evolution Association (EHBEA) is a UK-registered charity (Charity No. 1154585) that promotes research and collaboration in human behavioural and evolutionary sciences.

Author
- Amanda Rotella
- Treasurer, EHBEA
